< Review>
CoCo Fresh Tea & Juice has become my new favorite spot to hang out in Los Angeles, CA. With a space for a live performance from a small band, and seats near windows that allow you to glance at the busy side streets that line Colorado Blvd, this coffee house is the perfect place to relax, either with friends or without.</Review>

< Text>
I always order Black MilkTea or Milk tea with boba at any boba places, but this particular drink at this place is really good! Their boba is firm (not over cook) yet, chewy. Their black milktea has a real storing black tea which you don't usually get from other boba places. Overall, good quality drinks.< /Text>

[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMZR6cEK1FXUxoJuKSm21ktwMnNGbWvLMyxh6YD=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMJYXcx_n0JJjeElmxqs2zrWdsqwL3pOcSubSj_=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMDDQ25qQ2w4-Mc5nXs2p8waqiJC4DnEXBF2QXt=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN6X2dqRI7omWjjLEYsT4_q0Da-BQkL05oQWvW9=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPE3SFG3ye1bGfemMHzSUprmsqG2_0Bup-Zx6q6=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipO5fJu4oNclmsTcSiAs5vIO7yzjN6BYRkBIb3cF=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPj218rX_EZfRWosWIponGLcgQj3ZRjsPCn3R9t=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMiGIOn0LloXpbv92VIg4Ki4CM4emqld1F7-D8G=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMAIdqibcNgvtaF_K0AAbKPGK55UBFO3eY3b1LW=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipM7SxW1F4WzLliYQM9RHHDkfGD72BG--8CVFSTb=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pictures>
< Review>
After dining here with my girlfriend for a purposely planned, late Valentine's Day dinner. And having never heard of this place before making reservations, I am officially a fan of Woodlake Tavern!

To avoid the large number of people celebrating Valentine's Day on the 14th or the weekend after, my girlfriend I decided to move our celebration to two Saturday's after. And capped our day off by trying out a restaurant that we had not yet been to, but looked like it would be amazing....hence our trip to Woodlake Tavern.

I made reservations for 7, and once we arrived we were promptly seated at a table for two near the front door. It was pretty cold that day, and with patrons coming and going, I knew it would be better to be seated way from the entrance. That wasn't a problem here, and we quickly seated to  another table by the bar, for a more quiet and enjoyable night. Our waiter arrived shortly after we seated, to which we gave him our drink orders after some suggestions. And we took a little more time to look for the menu for what we wanted to eat. My girlfriend decided to get the Milagro Margarita which has grapefruit-brulee shrub, orange liqueur, and cranberry. While I chose thePurity Vodka Seasonal Mule which had fresh pomegranate seeds, pink peppercorn, cappelletti, and lime. Both versions of these classic drinks were new to us, but they both were really good.

We also decided to share an the chicken wings for an appetizer, and these wings were so delicious. They were covered in coffee bourbon bbq sauce and crispy garlic sauce, and we both were pleasantly surprised. And for our main course my girlfriend got the Shrimp & Grits, while I ordered the Steak Frites....both were AMAZING!!!

The Shrimp & Grits was served with jumbo Gulf Prawns, mixed in creamy grits, with sofrito and house cured bacon. And was  adorned with arugula to top it off. I tried a couple of bites and the seemed as if the bacon just melted in your mouth. And my Steak Frites was just out of this world. Imagine a medium rare/medium well chargrilled flatiron steak, with a demi-glace and brie butter, and served beef tallow fries. Before this night I didn't even know what beef tallow fries were, and so they cook the fries in a beef fat for a richer flavor. Those fries were hands down probably the best fries I've ever tasted. The salt just enhanced the unique flavor of the fries, that I don't know how they could have been any better. Besides the other amazing dishes, my girlfriend and I joked that we'd come back just for the fries alone!

During our evening of wonderful food, I was talking to my girlfriend about a drink that I hadn't had in years that was created locally in Davis, CA. I asked our waiter if he'd ever heard of it, to which he said he hadn't but he asked the bartender. He had and we conversed a bit and he made the drink for us, and because we'd had a good lighthearted conversation, when my girlfriend wanted to order another drink. The bartender was nice of enough to offer making her an apricot margarita that would be new to the menu for March's dinning selection. That drink too was really good. We finished the night off with the Bourbon Chocolate Parfait for dessert, which is a devils food cake, served with bourbon creme anglaise. It's very rich, so if you love chocolate then you'll love this dessert. It's might be a lot for one to have on their own because of how chocolaty it is, but sharing it was just perfect for us.

OVERALL: Love this place, it has amazing food and drinks, great atmosphere, deceptively large are I thought it was a really small place. But there's indoor and outdoor seating. So full in both you're looking at 100+ diners. Just a great experience and I look forward to going back!< /Review>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
I love Taco Tuesday at the upscale Woodlake Tavern, where you can feast on their amazingly tasty, slow-cooked beef brisket tacos for just $2 each.

I've never had anything like it ... I highly recommend them! Corner of Arden & Del Paso Blvd, formerly Enotria.

This place is known for their fine comfort food meats and expert chefs (pedigrees from Ella and The Firehouse) and wine selection. The Bee just gave them a glowing review, and word is getting out about this special spot.<//review>

<review>While the staff is very polite and squared-away and the food selection is nice, it is at a shocking price-point for its location. They are located in a quirky uptown spot that would be better fit for a craft brewery than a swanky wine-inspired place. Hipsters would probably sort of like the surrounding poverty.
Another oddity is that they have a very large patio with a great deal of potential. They've put in heat lamps, a fire pit, and a nice water feature, but it's strangely devoid of the amount of flora they could have. Further, the patio shares space with the pizza joint that is owned by the same people. However, you cannot sit on the patio and order a pizza, so you can order a pizza in the pizza shop and take it to the patio. Weird.
All that said I think the Happy Hour is pretty solid. The only issues with the food was a very sad pickel. Technically I don't think it was a pickle at all, just a sliced English cucumber.<//review><pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP0zAKYzk38PYzJN9d-XHSDW0mnTHN8TCL2QRZq=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMw35UHP_C9lLguBcI_-9hfX8kAIeNnbMQxnweN=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMJXKvbLI7vUjEJhSxFi7S4bueuoMOj76T4uUbv=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMWb_jW0zYKrl35XrvTlIkfml3V9LFS4KCX62Dw=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNDhW9f2yOmn9gavTAtIE_4lNd5xbkctw2M8KSl=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOf5qcVu0kPWnazu6o92LraZoAP-GajNPFF_YCX=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pictures>< Response>

Such a wonderful place.  I would recommend it highly.  The meal was incredible and the staff was wonderful.  Don't wait too long to try Woodlake Tavern.

We started our meal with an order of the Tallow Fries with a Small Salad that was put together perfectly.  We followed that with the Brisket with Mashed Potatoes and Macaroni and Cheese.  Everything was so good!.  We cannot wait until our next visit!</text>

1542936522396<//Date>
< rating>
5< /rating>
< Text>
"This is dancing food!" my husband exclaimed as he bit into the oxtail croquettes.
This diamond in the rough has a crisp,  clean,  and beautiful atmosphere. The bathroom was immaculate! There was even a clean changing room to freshen up.
Service: We were greeted by a friendly and welcoming host. We did not have a wait (not sure of normal busy hours, this was Wednesday around 7 or 8). Have you ever had a server who was not only friendly, offered excellent recommendations, and personable, but also seemed to genuinely enjoy the company of his/her guests? Michael was so friendly and welcoming to his guests (including us), that he deserves his own shoutout. I was visibly anxious (due to a really gross experience just two blocks up at a different establishment) and he didn't even bash the other business, he explained the way Sacramento is growing and said its improving. Definitely full of grace and class when he spoke with us. You're amazing! Thanks for making the experience memorable at Woodlake Tavern.
Drinks: My husband ordered a Thanksgiving specialty drink, Cranberry Sauce, Milagro Silver, Capelletti, Burly Juniper Cranberry Shrub, with Fresh Lime & Sweet Agave! Phenomenal! I finished my meal with their "Rabbit Down The Hole" cocktail. This was a very fragrant and flavorful mix,  it nails the name. There is not a better name: Gin & Amaretto mix with a honey carrot syrup,  with a sprig of thyme & a thin strip of carrot to garnish. I love savory drinks,  so if that's not your thing,  skip this and get a different specialty drink, but if you're like me or enjoy trying new drinks,  don't miss this one!
Food: We started with oxtail croquettes. White cheddar with Yukon gold potatoes and truffle aoili and chives sprinkled on top. The first bite had my husband beyond ecstatic. Hearty yet not overfilling. We ordered a Tavern Burger: beef cooked to order, covered with smoked white cheddar,  red leaf,  crispy onions, aioli,  and the most amazing savory with slight hint of sweet tomato marmalade! I can't express this enough,  it is amazing! Since I wasn't wanting such a hearty dinner,  I ordered the Impossible Burger: Vegan patty covered with crispy onions,  aioli, and that amazing flavorful tomato marmalade! There is something about that Vegan patty,  it was like an explosion of flavor in my mouth! We got salad instead of fries,  they top it with feta and your choice of dressing. Pretty good,  crisp & fresh. We shared some Macaroni & Cheese that was rich, creamy,  and crisp bread crumbs for a perfect texture that gives you that warm & gourmet home feeling.  We skipped on dessert for this time,  but, maybe next time!
Being stingy with 5 star reviews...this definitely gets 5 stars all around.< /Text>

<user_id>110476047534536824083<//user_id><user_name>Samuel Price<//user_name>< date>
1583641163972< /date>
<rate>4<//rate><Review>So this review was in some ways difficult to write fairly. To give context, my partner and I would regularly (once every other month) visit Uptown Pizza for a couple years. Uptown pizza (same owners, shared building) is now a part of Woodlake Tavern in that some of the pizzas are served on the Woodlake Tavern menu but Uptown Pizza on it's own is closed. There were a few reasons we loved Uptown Pizza. We loved having a really amazing Pizza place near us. We LOVED the Angry Hawaiian pizza. We really liked sitting in the back with the big tree and the absolutely beautiful mural on the wall.

So to start with, as usual, the food here was and is amazing, and all the staff we encountered were friendly and helpful. Tje servers were good and attentive and knew what they were doing. If all you care about is really good food at a decent price (and good servers and staff) then you wont be disappointed. Everything I've tried at Woodlake Tavern and Uptown Pizza has been amazing. So 5 stars if you just care about food (EXCEPT that the Angry Hawaiian is NOT on the list of regular pizzas served anymore. Apparently they may consider adding this back as a special, but that doesnt interest me as I'm not going somewhere for a special once in a while, I'm going to a restaurant because of the regularity of my favorite dish).

The reason I give 4 stars is because they have enclosed the previous outdoor space, and removed the amazing mural... the whole outdoor area is now a muted grayish green color with nothing at all special about the walls (except for a nice water feature and fireplace on one end). I would have kept the mural, and added murals to the rest of the walls to give it character.

There isn't really any good space for the outdoor games that used to be there either. And worst of all, the combination of changes makes the previous relaxing and unique outdoor space feel like a food court. And believe me though, the prices are not food court prices.

I understand these decisions were probably made to fulfill the majority of customers needs and I'm sure it all made business sense. I cant blame them for making the changes if it was a financial decision. BUT, I wont be coming back. Well, if a friend really wanted to go and invited us, I'd have no problem eating there again because the food really is great. But the aspects that really drew us back to this location are now gone unfortunately. Now we go back to the seeming neverending search for a "regular" spot that satisfies us the way Uptown Pizza used to.

Good luck, we really do wish them the best, as it's nice to have restaurants and other businesses opening up in that area, changing the neighborhood.</Review><Pics>None</Pics><response>None< /response><gmapID>0x809ad745a7b2a31f:0xcc76334f5612a8ca< /gmapID></record></dataset><record>

< text>
I found this gem of a restaurant while searching for a quiet, cozy place to celebrate my 40th wedding anniversary and it did not disappoint!
We were greeted warmly by the maitre d' as if we were old friends and then seated immediately.  Our server Karishma was excellent -- very friendly, helpful and knowledgeable.  My wife was excited about the Prime Rib Single weekend special which was a good-sized portion that was delicious.  I had the Brisket Sandwich with a side salad.  Both the Sandwich and the Salad were excellent.  We also shared an order of Smoked Onion Rings which were also very tasty.  My wife loved the ranch dipping sauce while I requested something different.  Karishma suggested an aioli sauce which had just enough kick for my tastebuds.
We had to park a couple of blocks away due to an event going on nearby; however, it was a pleasant night for a stroll.
Already we are looking forward to another visit to the fantastic Woodlake Tavern!< /text>

< text>
My best friend and I are searching for the perfect Happy Hour experience.  Our 1st impressions at Woodlake Tavern: Service staff, very friendly and welcoming.

Pro's: Large Happy Hour portions and excellent dirty martini's.

Con's: The Happy Hour wings & ribs were tough. I dont believe in tearing meat from bones like our ancestors.  Succulent, fall off the bone ribs are the only way ribs should ever be served.  And the chicken wings were well seasoned but a bit rubbery for my preference.  Crispy is the way to go with wings.
Plus, we ordered "well" dirty martinis for happy hour drinks, priced @ $6 per but were charged $8 per. When we disputed this on the bill we were told that there is a $2 upcharge for "martinis". This was not advised when we ordered.  Bummer.
We'll keep looking for our perfect Happy Hour fit.
Best of luck Woodlake in improving your systems and sorting out your menu. üòâ<//text>

< Review>
I found this Gem while looking for new restraunts to try that weren't on the beaten path of downtown. We were comming for happy hour and I didn't know what to expect on a Friday night so I made a reservation from the website. When we got there we waited like literally 2 seconds to be seated. We decided to sit on the patio which turned out to be a little chilly but they had heaters which turned on for a which made me think this would be great for a summer evening that got breazy. We ordered the brisket sliders, the burger with beef talo fries and a side of onion rings. Everything was delicious. I also ordered their cocktail of the day which featured gin and carrot juice honey syrup! phenomenal! and I'm not really a gin drinker. Our waitress Nicole was also awesome  checking on us frequently, but giving us space to enjoy our date. I would definitely come again and bring friends for happy hour or dinner or both!< /Review>

105873562273259058072<//user_id>
< Name>
John McDonald<//Name>
<Date>1537814580434<//Date>< rating>
5< /rating>
< Review>
Absolutely sumptuous! This off-the-beaten path restaurant is definitely worth the trip. We found their simple California inspired southern comfort food menu to be delightful and matched only by the spirited and warm staff and quaintly decorated surroundings. On warm evenings their patio is the perfect spot to imbibe in a refreshing cocktail while devouring anything on this amazing menu.

We tried the summer Gnocchi, their Korean sticky ribs and, of course, their BBQ sampler platter. All of our food was delivered at the same time and arrived piping hot to our table. Great detail was paid to the presentation of our food. Excellent execution by the kitchen staff.

The Korean ribs were out of this world delicious. Perfectly prepared to fall off the bone and coated in a sweet and sticky sauce that will make your mouth water. The BBQ sampler was an lively mix of various proteins with corn bread. If you like corn bread, you MUST have the corn bread at woodlake. It is, without a shadow of a doubt, the finest corn bread I've even eaten. The crust was slightly crunchy but the inside was soft and moist. An absolute tribute to what corn bread should be. The sausage was good but tasted like an expensive beef hot dog. The mustard braised chicken was very good and I don't even like mustard. Their standard pork ribs were outstanding with a very light smoke flavor and delicious sweet bbq sauce. I'm not a fan of heavy smoke flavor but wood does an excellent job of balancing very light smoke with the sweet bbq sauce. They were fall-off-the-bone perfect.

Our dessert was just as well prepared as our dinner. We tried the potted cheese cake which we're going to call the peach cobbler cheese cake. The peach was delicious and fresh and the cheesecake was excellent. Very smooth and creamy with the mild tart cheesecake flavor you'd expect. Our only wish would be to provide slightly more graham crumble to the top or, perhaps, add a butter crumb layer at the bottom. We also had the banana ice cream. While the appearance was a little southern cafe, it's flavors and textures were very well balanced. Little surprises await you in this dessert and they're wonderful.

The only misstep of the entire evening was a single, ill prepared, mojito which was short on rum and very long mint. They were happy to remake it for us and immediately corrected the issue.

In short, Woodlake Tavern is an absolute hidden gem with perfectly prepared meals and smiling, happy and knowledgeable staff. We cannot wait to return...perhaps tonight.

We would like to thank Michael, our server, for making our meal unforgettable.</Review>

<rate>5</rate><Review>I had such an amazing dining experience here.

Upon entering, the first thing I noticed was the small setting. Despite being new, there was no wait. Still, the ambiance is very elegant. Nice open bar and a few tables. There is even a large, open patio area in the rear for larger events. Quickly, I was able to get a booth that sat my girlfriend and I next to each other.

We ordered a few things.

Carnivore sampler: An array of meats that include ribs, chicken wings, and sausage. Served with pickled vegitables. Everything tasted wonderful, but the wings stood out. Sweet and delicious.

Tavern burger: I ordered this with fries...Which were amazing! The fries perfectly complemented the tasty flavors in the burger. The burger itself has to be one of the best burgers in Sacramento and I don't deny that this maybe a great contender for the annual burger battle.

Chicken pot pie: Such a large serving! Golden flakey crust, a flavorful filling with a hint of curry. Reminded me of a large empanada.

Mashed potatoes and gravy: a hearty bowl size. Savory and creamy. Too much goodness here.

Banana Ice cream pie: our server recommend this to us and it did not disappoint. The perfect end to our meal. Banana Ice cream on top of an Oreo crust, smothered with whipped cream, caramel and chocolate?! Yes!

The service is fantastic and the staff is incredibly pleasant. Immediately after they served me and my girlfriend our food, they genuinely appear happy at our admiration for the food.

This place has set the bar as my new favorite restaurant in Sacramento.<//Review>< Pictures>

[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMkWWSSHuh6q1uAmVmOceliyi1FRpi4XONa3TyN=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /pictures>

< UserId.>
112516491002546219221</UserId.>
< Name>
kathy kim caldwell< /Name>
<Time>1493952246163<//Time>< rate>
5< /rate>
< text>
My first piece of advice if you want to know what to order is: 1) order the tallow fries. Then 2) order the banana cream pie.
You won't regret them!
Next get the chicken wings and the Mac and Cheese because Woodlake Tavern is all about comfort food that tastes amazing.

The service was great--not too overbearing just attentive enough that I had a full water glass, a drink and an offer of dessert after digesting for 10-15 minutes. Our server was patient with our party of 7, and was quick to answer our questions and easy going.

The venue is well designed with a classy inside, and an amazing outdoor area with the most comfortable  dining chairs I've ever sat in. They are pet friendly outside just please make sure your pup is well behaved :) You can also see the stack from the smoker that apparently had to be placed by crane into its niche. It's pretty cool!

But the highlight of my dinner was the food!! Here is a rundown of everyone's meal.

Beef tallow fries (see first sentence above)
Mac and cheese--amazeballs!!!
Chicken wings--what the what. Perfectly glazed and crisp with a tart and sweet well rounded flavor that complimented my fries perfectly.
Chicken pot pie--they weren't kidding when they said it's the size of a whole pie. It arrived and I admitted defeat before I even took a bite it was so huge! It also had tons of meat and those glorious huge English peas with parsnips, potatoes and carrots. All topped with a buttery crust!
Seasonal asparagus--so fresh and perfectly grilled.
Steak frites-- my husband remarked that the beef was perfectly cooked and tender.
Burger--my friend noted it was one of the best burgers he has ever had. And he is a chef and is serious about his food so I knew he wasn't making it up.
BBQ Ribs--for those in the know, Thursday is $1 rib night. So I added ribs to my gargantuan meal because there was no way I was going to walk out without eating their ribs they slow cook on the premises. The result? A perfectly cooked meaty morsel with a smoky, peppery, tangy vinegary sauce that reminds me of KC
style sauce.

The Crown Jewels of the night were our desserts.
Banana ice cream pie (see second sentence above)
Strawberry shortcake--perfection
Meyer Lemon cheesecake-- not too sweet with just the right amount of lemon tartness it is one of the best lemon cheesecakes I've ever had. Texture similar to NY style without the heft, which made it smooth and easy to eat.
Chocolate parfait--a little bourbon and a little chocolate. Creamy and not too sweet it hit the spot.

Bottom line, head over to Woodlake Tavern because the owners Deneb and Elizabeth have poured their hearts and souls into the first of their trio of restaurants coming to Sac. A much needed breath of fresh air of quality sourced foods made with thoughtful flavors and experiences in mind.
Sacramento is lucky to have them and I can't wait to see them continue to grow!<//text>

<Time>1514612434200</Time><Rating>5</Rating>< Review>
I have been eating here once or twice a month for over a year. Only once have I ever had an issue with the food taking a long time to be ready, but on that one occasion the staff was so friendly and apologetic about it and gave me a free entree coupon for my next visit. Otherwise the food is always ready within 15 minutes. It's not fast food, it's made fresh to order so of course it takes some time to cook. It's well worth the wait though because the food is great. No, it's not authentic Chinese food, but it's freshly cooked, tastes good, and doesn't cost a fortune. As with any restaurant, they have a few dishes that really make them shine. You need to order the House Special Chicken, Garlic Chicken, chow mein, egg rolls, and cream cheese wontons! I don't understand how anyone could say Panda Express is better when their food sits under heat lamps all day.< /Review>

< Time>
1539405429990<//Time>
< Name>
Robin Whang</Name>
< Review>
As you walk into the cheerfully red Deli Counter, you notice the backsplash along the wall: it's a map of LA county, with stars denoting noted sandwich joints like Langer's, Philippe, Bay Cities. Right by the entrance, you then see a stylized C by the section of the 710 fwy, for The Deli Counter itself. The design is at once an homage to legends and an announcement of the shop's aspirations: To be on the top shelf as the other stars on the wall.

A buddy of mine and I went for the most popular option, based on the photos attached in Yelp: the DTLA Pastrami.  And it did not disappoint. Inches-thick mound of Pastrami laced with Russian slaw and a slightly melting slab of Swiss cheese, wrapped tightly in a French roll.

With the Pastrami deliciously warm and the slaw providing a cool, pickled backstop of flavor, the sandwich disappears in a food inhaling instant - along with the attendant chips and drink if you order the combo for $2.50 more. It makes you look up, hankering for more. But take a deep breath, and wait a couple minutes - just as quickly as you ate that sandwich, so will the food coma hit as you realize you just devoured a pretty hefty meal.

Shake off the nap, and stumble out the door back to work - And remember to revisit this place when the craving for a sandwich calls your name.

Does it live up to its desire to be mentioned in the same breath as the other esteemed sandwich places? If they keep showing that same focus and care, I think it will.< /Review>

<review>Great hidden gem in the city of Carson!!! My office is within walking distance of this place so I remember when it used to be a quiznos there.  They are actually way better than quiznos because it is real authentic sandwiches which is hard to find these days.  I have had the grilled cheese with avocado and bacon and the turkey club and both were amazing!  The owner James is a great guy too that's who actually made my sandwich.  I have brought a few of my clients and they are addicted.  Bonus is that they have thai iced tea!!! < text>
I wanted to buy 2 dirt bikes from them and contacted them twice through their website but never heard back.

- What are you looking for?
Hi, I'm looking for a KLX140RF and a CRF250F.
- Sorry we don't have any in stock.
Ohk, anything we can do to get them?
- No
Ohk, bye then.
- Bye

I suppose Fremont Honda Kawasaki probably have enough business on their plate and are ok leaving a few customers on the table.< /text>

<UserId.>114803586439456922177<//UserId.>< Name>
BAM! Buy A Mattress< /Name>
<Time>1517500211044< /Time>< Rate>
5</Rate>
< review>
I am not a shopper. I'm a buyer.  So when I look online for something, I check the hours for the store and I expect the store to be open.   People expect that from me at my Fremont store BAM! Buy A Mattress (gratuitous plug, lol).

So when I arrived at 6:04pm at Fremont Honda Kawasaki Suzuki and the door was chained, I made that little hop that kids make when they're about to throw a tantrum. I just needed a battery so I tapped on the door and the man in the motorcycle outfit came to the door and made a hand motion that they were closed. I held up my phone, pointed and said Google indicates that you're open till 7pm.  His response was unexpected he shook his head but open the door and said, "How can we help you?"  Explaining the situation, he stopped me and signaled the parts manager who is also suited up in riding gear ready to leave. Obviously not thrilled he explained he had to restart the computer, clock in, look up the part manually and he got started. At that moment my phone rang.  I had to take a sales call and put him off.  He listened to my spiel and realized that I was still working too.

I got the right part at the best price available, better than Cycle Gear, better than the big box stores, better than the mom and pop stores and I got amazing service.

Their hours are Tuesday through Friday 10 to 6, Saturday 10 to 5.

I want to thank the manager and the parts manager of Fremont Honda Kawasaki Suzuki Motorcycle for solving my problem after they were officially closed.

They were very professional and I'm very happy.

Want to know how I know I was very happy?   It is because I was glad to give them my money.

I highly recommend you buy your parts for your motorsport vehicle from Fremont Honda Kawasaki Suzuki Motorcycle.  I am a first-time customer and now a customer for life.< /review>

<userid>106670594712469132399</userid>< Name>
Miranda Jayne</Name>
<Time>1403418545023<//Time><rating>2< /rating>< text>
I brought in my 2007 Honda Rebel CMX250 after issues with the bike running, stalling on its own (sounded like it was running out of gas), and having this issue again and again intermittently, I brought my bike in to this shop to see if it could be fixed, or at least the service guys could figure out the problem. They changed my spark plugs for $100 (admittedly, they didn't look that great, but they certainly weren't dead, and changing the spark plugs didn't match up at all with the description of the issue I told them -- a possible vacuum creation). They told me everything was fine with the bike.

Wary, I took my bike back home and even went shopping. I started the bike up again the next morning and after a few minutes, the bike shut down. I managed to get my bike back home, pulling off the road several times, and called the shop.

Thankfully, Fremont Honda & Kawasaki picked up my bike from my house to bring it to the shop. I caught a ride with a friend to get there, where I told them my bike had the exact same problem they said had been fixed the previous day.

One of the guys there said it should be fine (I was adamant that it wasn't), and they said it's okay if I leave my bike overnight and they'd test it in the morning. Sure enough, I come in the next day, and they've got the bike running. I rode around for about 15-20 minutes to make sure. Take it home, next day arrives, and..

The problem STILL isn't fixed. I'm extremely frustrated at this point. I don't bother bringing it back to the shop and decide to dig online to find the problem on a Honda Rebel forum.

Eventually, I and my boyfriend discovered it was a vacuum problem due to the poor quality of emission filters installed on California models of the Honda Rebel to meet California's emission standards.
----
All in all, since the problem was intermittent, I can't really blame the guys for not being able to figure out it was the filter all along.

I am disappointed that they pretty much guaranteed my bike would be okay after changing the spark plugs even after a long description of the problem (sounded like it would run out of gas, switched to reserve, nothing.. probably a vacuum) that changing the spark plugs would likely have nothing to do with.

If you are having an issue with your bike, I would recommend trying to find the problem on a motorcycle online forum first and finding a resolution BEFORE going in to this shop.

I still go to this shop from time to time to pick up supplies, i.e. air filters and oil filters, but it is not the best for service.<//text>

After several conversations over the phone and 1 impromptu visit to see the showroom I made an appt to take a test drive 2 motorcycles.   I drove 110 miles roundtrip to get there only to find out one of the bikes was sold and I couldnt test drive the other because I didn't bring my own gear. He then offered to sell me brand new stuff at a modest discount just to take a test drive.

<Rate>5< /Rate><Text>Extra Space Storage On N. River Rd. is a great location. We have had two storage units there for the past eight years.
They recently repainted everything and it looks great. The location is very convenient and large delivery trucks can get easily in and out.
The managers, Jeff and Sabina, are terrific. They have repeatedly gone way above and beyond in helping us.
Occasionally, a pallet delivery will arrive at an unexpected time. When that happens, Jeff or Sabina are kind enough to give me a call so I don‚Äôt miss the delivery.
Recently, I had an early three pallet delivery, which was due the following day, so I was left with no help.
Sabina called to let me know my delivery had arrived early.
I quickly gathered the things I needed in order to receive the order and raced over to Extra Space Storage.

< Review>
Owning a 25ft RV I have been a tenant at Extra Space Storage on North River Road in Oceanside on and off for five years. The place is well managed, the staff is friendly and accommodating. The gate access hours from 6:00 a.m. to 9:00 p.m. work well for me. I like the fact that there is a dump station, RV/truck wash and running water. It is kept very clean and for the most part everything works. Like any storage facility the rates will slightly increase every six months but Erika and Sabina in the office will do their best to accommodate you. They were able to use a promotional rate to keep my monthly rates down. I highly recommend this place.</Review>

< text>
I have used this particular storage facility two times now in the last nine years.  There is a 24/7 live on site manager.  The gates only operate for a certain time each day, stopping individuals from trying to get access to the storages at night.  And it's get the first month free, that really is a nice tokens of appreciation from the Company.  If you have personal insurance on your belongings, like Renters or look Homeowners insurance, be sure to bring your policy if you are getting a rental.  Extra Space REQUIRES you have insurance, and they will make you purchase theirs.  Overall it's a safe place to store your belongings.  Clean and well maintained buildings and storages.<//text>

Once I came I saw there was a totally different brand new lock and new my valuables were gone. Couldn't check until the next day and let the staff cut the lock. Yup the reason I got this 5x5 unit to hold my belongings was gone. Told them they can throw the rest away, no reason to have storage now that my most expensive possessions are stolen.
What really shocked me was that the property only has cameras in the entrances and exits. NONE in the storage buildings making it prime for theft. So chances of finding him? Slim. There were 2 other units stolen from as well in the same F building. Just poor security.

This place is phenomenal.

< review>
Great place, amazing location and tasty food.

Great tasty Mexican food, they served breakfast till 10.00 am , lunch, happy hour and dinner.

They open weekdays 7.00 am and closes at 9.00 pm.

They are priced reasonably. And have wide variety of tacos , burritos , salads chips and salsas.

They serve bear, amazing margarita!!!

They have ample seating inside and patio seats.

I love their breakfast burrito, taco salads and Gordita!

This place is amazing spot for happy hour for its location, choices of drinks, space to get together.</review>

< Text>
A best place for a quick and tasty and sumptuous lunch.
I just loved their indoor as well as the out door decor.
They have and indoor bar and dining with authentic Mexican music.
The menu is small that includes tacos,carnitas, burritos and salads with vegetable's,chicken etc.

We had a vegetarian plate and a vegetarian burrito both of them were lip smacking

Don't forget their hot sauce.. a must try.

In the out door I liked their idea of reusing the salsa tins for storing tissues and forks.< /Text>

This place was very disappointing. We order 2 carne asada plates and 2 carne asada burritos. <text>I've been to uno dos tacos so many times and have always had a great experience- the food and especially the margaritas are so yummy and I'd recommend it to anyone looking for a quality Mexican food place in SOMA. However I was sorely disappointed today from the service my friends and I got. We arrived at uno dos at 7:30 (1.5 hours before closing) and we were enjoying some margaritas at 9:15 when a waitress came and took a half-full pitcher away and my half-drunk glass that I was about to grab! They never gave us any warning that they were about to close and they didn't even give us a chance to finish the $30 pitcher we got! < review>
Great place to go after work for happy hour! The food is great, the happy hour runs late, and it's reasonably priced (a rarity for the area). Tons of seating available both inside and outside, but it can get crowded with the after-work crowd so be prepared if you're trying to fit a large group. < review>
Get the fish tacos. So good.
I love the outdoor patio seating, perfectly shaded and a bit of a beach town feel off of busy Market St - complimented further by a bucket of beer. Bonus points for accepting SF weather and having a bevy of blankets available for when the evening grows chilly. While ordering may make you think you are in a Ch, you wont find rice anywhere on the premises. Select your meat (or go vegetarian) then the presentation: taco, burrito, salad or plate.</review>

< Text>
Simply Fantastic! Take the "healthy" style of Chipotle and combine it with authentic Mexican food at a similar price point (if not cheaper), but better tasting.

Then add the tequila bar, beers, the energetic atmosphere, and the fact that they make their own tortillas! You could not ask any more of a play of this style.

Want to eat outside but it is cold? Grab one of their blankets from inside and stay warm!< /Text>

<Review>Unfortunately I forgot to take pictures of the food. We arrived on a Thursday around 6 p.m. expecting a 30 minute wait or more. We immediately found tables ordered our food and was eating with in just a few minutes. As a self-proclaimed Taco specialist and chips and salsa connoisseur. I can't say that it was my favorite but I can say that it was pretty tasty. For being Gringo style tacos I did find them very flavorful but a little salty. When things are salty it does concern me as to the quality. Happy hour had affordable beers and menu items and there tacos were not overly priced. I was not a big fan of the gordita Style I prefer them to be stuffed instead of just 2 round discs of Masa. The gorditas should be called something else as they are by definition not gorditas, gorditas should be stuffed. Would I eat here again? Yes if it was right by me, but I won't make a special trip back.<//Review>< gmap_id>

<name>Alexaundria Wood</name><date>1501691439939</date>< Rating>
5</Rating>
<review>Five stars all DAY LONG. Of all the places we ate this trip this is the one I wish we could go back to! The burritos were amazing, all the flavors worked well together but didn't muddle into one flavor like so many other places. My husband had the carnitas and they were perfectly tender and the burrito didn't skimp on the meat.
I had the carne asada and it was tender and soft, not chewy, great grilled flavor, and my husband who usually doesn't like carne asada asked for a second one bite! Happy hour has a larger guacamole and chips for $5 and it was perfect to split between two and served immediately.
We came in at 8:30 but we're served quickly and had plenty of time to eat before closing.
And can I sing praises for the prices?! The first affordable meal we had that delivered on satisfaction as well. Keep doing what you're doing Uno Dos.< /review>< Pics>

They have similar options to Chipotle, but with more proteins (lengua, fish) and fresh corn tortillas. I like the Steak, Carnitas and Fish Tacos. The plates are nice too. I wish they had a salsa bar with more variety though.</Review>
